                    <h2 class="display-4">Introduction</h2>
                    <p class="lead">Web development is an ever-evolving field, and staying up-to-date with the latest trends is crucial for any developer. This blog explores some of the most exciting developments and predicts where the web is heading in the near future.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="display-5">Emerging Technologies</h3>
                    <p>Several technologies are making waves in the web development community. These include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Artificial Intelligence:</strong> AI is being integrated into web applications to provide personalized experiences.</li>
                        <li><strong>Progressive Web Apps (PWAs):</strong> PWAs offer a native app-like experience while running in a web browser.</li>
                        <li><strong>WebAssembly:</strong> This technology allows developers to run high-performance code on the web.</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h3 class="display-5">Future Trends</h3>
                    <p>Looking ahead, we can expect several trends to dominate the web development landscape:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li><strong>Increased Focus on User Experience:</strong> As competition grows, delivering an exceptional user experience will be key.</li>
                        <li><strong>Enhanced Security Measures:</strong> With rising cyber threats, web security will continue to be a major focus.</li>
                        <li><strong>Integration of IoT:</strong> The Internet of Things (IoT) will drive more connected and interactive web applications.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h2 class="display-4">Conclusion</h2>
                    <p>Web development is rapidly advancing, and staying informed about new technologies and trends is essential for developers. By embracing these changes, we can build better, more innovative web experiences.</p>
